=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nbh1665702675570.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nbh1665702675570.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nbh1665702675570.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"nbh1665702675570\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You must define a print job model before you can print data from Form components. </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__context_w704ab1b5b1_w705ab1b5_w706ab1\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__note_w707ab1b5b1b1_w708ab1b5b1_w709ab1b5_w710ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Printing data in\n            the Uniface IDE is only possible in the editors available from the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More\n               Editors</span> menu.</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__li_d28181e1_d28182e1_d28183e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Uniface IDE, choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Setup</span> from the main menu (\n               ≡ ). </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__li_d28184e1_d28185e1_d28186e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Clear the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Job Model</span> field. Then click\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">&gt;&gt;</span> to display a list of available models.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__li_d28187e1_d28188e1_d28189e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">New</span> to open the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Define Print Job\n                  Model</span> dialog.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">You can also select a model and click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Edit</span> to change an\n               existing model.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__li_d28190e1_d28191e1_d28192e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__p_d65069e1_d65070e1_d65071e1\">Specify the name and other details of the print\n               job model.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">At minimum, you must specify a value in <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Name</span> and the device\n               translation table in <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Device Type</span>. Options include:<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__li_d28193e1_d28194e1_d28195e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"upo1665702675641.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/upo1665702675641.html\" title=\"Name of the print job model.\">Name</a>—print job\n                     model name</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__li_d28196e1_d28197e1_d28198e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xmq1665702675709.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xmq1665702675709.html\" title=\"Name of the device translation table to use for this print job model.\">Device Type</a>—device\n                     translation table to use for this print job model</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__li_d28199e1_d28200e1_d28201e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ymx1665702675781.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ymx1665702675781.html\" title=\"The Print Queue specifies the destination of the printed output.\">Print Queue</a>—destination of the printed output</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__li_d28202e1_d28203e1_d28204e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xhc1665702675851.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xhc1665702675851.html\" title=\"Print options provide additional parameters for the operating system print command, or the command specified in Print Queue.\">Print Options</a>—additional operating system options</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__li_d28205e1_d28206e1_d28207e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ozu1665702675920.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ozu1665702675920.html\" title=\"A device mode is a collection of predefined page formatting attributes for a device translation table. It controls the number of columns and lines, character width, line depth, and page orientation. Each printer device translation table has its own set of modes.\">Device Mode</a>—predefined page formatting for a specific <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Device\n                     Type</span></li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__li_d28208e1_d28209e1_d28210e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lwg1665702675989.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lwg1665702675989.html\" title=\"Margins of the printed output are expressed in terms of lines and characters.\">Margins</a>—margins\n                     of the printed output, expressed in terms of lines and characters</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__li_d28211e1_d28212e1_d28213e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print using\n                     colors</span></li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__li_d28214e1_d28215e1_d28216e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print black on\n                     white</span></li>\n</ul></div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__li_d28217e1_d28218e1_d28219e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Clear the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Device Type</span> field or enter a profile (for example\n                  <kbd class=\"ph userinput\">P_Data *</kbd>).</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__step_w711ab1b5b3c11_w712ab1b5b3_w713ab1b5_w714ab1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">&gt;&gt;</span> to display the list of available device\n               translation tables.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__step_w715ab1b5b3c13_w716ab1b5b3_w717ab1b5_w718ab1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Select a table and click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span>. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__li_d28220e1_d28221e1_d28222e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span> to save the print job model.\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Example: Typical Print Job Model for Windows</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\">For example, the following print job model uses the enhanced printing device\n                  translation table for Windows (<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Device Type</span>:\n                     <code class=\"ph codeph\">P_MSWINX</code>) and invokes the Windows Print dialog box so that the\n                  user can configure and control printing (<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Queue</span>:\n                     <code class=\"ph codeph\">printman</code>).</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__fig_m3b_xwh_vwb\">\n<br/><img alt=\"Define Print Job Model example\" class=\"image\" id=\"nbh1665702675570__image_n3b_xwh_vwb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/printjobmodel_win.png?_LANG=enus\"/><br/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/guw1665702607063.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Print Job Models</a><p>A print job model is a named collection of printer attributes that determine how and where Uniface forms or reports are printed, including details of the device type, margins, and so on. A print job model must be available before you can print.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qdk1665702675095.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define a Logical Printer</a><p>On Windows, you can define a logical printer, which is a named collection of printer settings for a physical printer. You can define more than one logical printer for the same physical printer.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530181\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530181\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define a Print Job Model Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 You must define a print job model before you can print data from Form components. Note: Printing data in the Uniface IDE is only possible in the editors available from the More Editors menu. In the Uniface IDE, choose Print Setup from the main menu ( ≡ ). Clear the Print Job Model field. Then click >> to display a list of available models. Click New to open the Define Print Job Model dialog. You can also select a model and click Edit to change an existing model. Specify the name and other details of the print job model. At minimum, you must specify a value in Name and the device translation table in Device Type . Options include: Name —print job model name Device Type —device translation table to use for this print job model Print Queue —destination of the printed output Print Options —additional operating system options Device Mode —predefined page formatting for a specific Device Type Margins —margins of the printed output, expressed in terms of lines and characters Print using colors Print black on white Clear the Device Type field or enter a profile (for example P_Data * ). Click >> to display the list of available device translation tables. Select a table and click OK . Click OK to save the print job model. Example: Typical Print Job Model for Windows For example, the following print job model uses the enhanced printing device translation table for Windows ( Device Type : P_MSWINX ) and invokes the Windows Print dialog box so that the user can configure and control printing ( Print Queue : printman ). Related Links Print Job Models A print job model is a named collection of printer attributes that determine how and where Uniface forms or reports are printed, including details of the device type, margins, and so on. A print job model must be available before you can print. Define a Logical Printer On Windows, you can define a logical printer, which is a named collection of printer settings for a physical printer. You can define more than one logical printer for the same physical printer. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}